<headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued August 03 at 4:31PM MDT until August 03 at 4:45PM MDT by NWS Boulder</headline>
<description>...A SEVERE THUNDERSTORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 445 PM MDT
FOR NORTHWESTERN ELBERT COUNTY...
At 431 PM MDT, a severe thunderstorm was located over Kiowa, or 35
miles northeast of Colorado Springs, moving east at 15 mph.
HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and quarter size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees. Hail damage to
vehicles is expected. Hail may accumulate on roadways
causing hazardous travel.
Locations impacted include...
Kiowa.
HAIL THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX HAIL SIZE...1.00 IN
WIND THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX WIND GUST...60 MPH</description>
<instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
